universum.studios.android.setting

Class SettingSpinnerPreference

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.preference.Preference
      • universum.studios.android.setting.SettingPreference
        • universum.studios.android.setting.SettingSpinnerPreference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Preference>

    public class SettingSpinnerPreference
extends SettingPreference
    A SettingPreference implementation that provides Spinner widget with its related functionality. Entries that should be available for selection as drop down items of the Spinner widget may be specified via setEntries(CharSequence[]) along with theirs corresponding entry values that should be specified via setEntryValues(CharSequence[])

    This preference implementation by default displays a single Spinner widget with a primary view containing title text of the preference and summary text which corresponds to the current selected entry value. The preferred entry value may be specified via setValue(String) and obtained via getValue().

    Default value

    Default value for this preference is parsed as String which should contain a single entry value that should be by default selected. See TypedArray.getString(int).

    Xml attributes

    See SettingPreference, SettingSpinnerPreference Attributes

    Default style attribute

    uiSettingSpinnerPreferenceStyle
    Author:
    Martin Albedinsky

        public void setEntryValues(@Nullable
                           CharSequence[] entryValues)
        Specifies an array of entry values where each value should be associated with corresponding entry from the entries array specified via setEntries(CharSequence[]).

        Note, that this method does not check if the entries and entry values arrays are consistent, that is that they are equal in length.

        Parameters:
        entryValues - The desired array of values associated with entries. May be null to clear the current ones.
        See Also:
        R.attr.entryValues
